Japan has provided some 500 million US dollar fund for tsunami- affected countries including Indonesia, the Maldives and Sri Lanka.
Nearly 500,000 people were made homeless after tsunami swept Aceh province, in Indonesia on Dec. 26, ministry of information and communication said on Wednesday.
The sources said as part of the planned 1,000 metric tons of HEB, the government is contemplating of sending several hundred tons of HEB to Sri Lanka, Indonesia and the Maldives in the coming weeks.
Bangladesh would airlift and ship 1, 000 metric tons of high energy biscuits (HEB) for the tsunami victims of Indonesia and Sri Lanka this week.
